fetch_ticket.result:
Please look at this Trace I couldn't able to find where this request is redirected to. This is a CLM Demo Trace; Can you please take a look why OtlpSpanEvents do not have span attributes  HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION ?
Query from OtlpSpanEvents https://kazmon.docusign.net/Kusto?queryId=20250513015129-4146728714337517111
Query from RequestEvents link here
As you know that these are very important span attributes for us to assess the impact and for investigation of an issue, could you please ensure these attributes are available in OtlpspanEvents? Thank you!

 

Query from OtlpSpanEvents



OtlpSpanEvents
| where Timestamp between (datetime('2025-05-10T02:55:40.207396Z')..datetime('2025-05-10T08:25:40.207396Z'))
| where Environment == "Demo"
//| where url_path contains "/clm/SSO/SSOEndpoint.ashx"
| where url_path == "/clm/Documents/BrowseDocuments.aspx"
| where http_status_code > 200
| limit 100
 

Query from RequestEvents



let _startTime=datetime(2025-05-10T02:55:40.207396Z);
let _endTime = datetime(2025-05-10T08:25:40.207396Z);
RequestEvents
| where Timestamp between (_startTime .. _endTime) and Environment=="Demo"
| where Application == "clm-web"
| where HTTP_RESPONSE_STATUS_CODE == "302" and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION contains "Error"
| limit 100


Acceptance Criteria

HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION should be available as span_attributes

result.semantic_description: Add HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION as attributes on all CLM web request spans so they show up in OtlpSpanEvents.

sub_tasks.description:
Identify where OpenTelemetry is configured and where HTTP server Activities are currently enriched in clm-web.
 • Search for “AddOpenTelemetry”, “UseOpenTelemetry”, “Activity.SetTag(” in Startup.cs, Program.cs, and *Extensions.cs.
 • Confirm whether we already have a custom ActivityEnricher or Middleware (e.g. TracingMiddleware, OpenTelemetryHttpMiddleware).
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Exact location(s) and lifecycle hooks for server request span creation are documented in the ticket wiki.

sub_tasks.name: Security & schema pre-checks
sub_tasks.description:
Confirm emitting these headers is allowed.
 • Review with Infosec/Privacy whether Referer or Location might contain PII.
 • If needed, define sanitisation (e.g. strip query string after ‘?’).
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Signed-off security comment in ticket or ADR attached.

sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Both tags appear when running a local Fiddler/Postman redirect test and are visible in OpenTelemetry collector debug exporter.

sub_tasks.name: Guardrails & sampling
sub_tasks.description:
Ensure the new tags are not dropped by processors:
 • Update attribute-filter processor allow-list (if any).
 • Update span-sampling logic to keep 3xx responses.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Span with new tags successfully forwarded through OTLP exporter in lower env.

sub_tasks.name: Update Kusto mapping
sub_tasks.description:
Add columns to OtlpSpanEvents table mapping:
```
.alter table OtlpSpanEvents ingest json mapping 'otel_span_mapping' '[ ...
   {"column":"HTTP_REFERER", "path":"$.attributes.HTTP_REFERER", "datatype":"string"},
   {"column":"HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION", "path":"$.attributes.HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION", "datatype":"string"}
]'
```
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Ingest test span via ADX “.ingest inline” and query verifies the two new columns are populated.

sub_tasks.name: Automated tests
sub_tasks.description:
Add/extend tests:
 • Unit test for middleware: mock HttpContext, verify Activity tags.
 • Integration test using TestServer that issues redirect 302.
 • Kusto schema test in CI to ensure mapping contains new columns.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: CI pipeline green with new tests passing.

sub_tasks.name: Deploy to Demo env
sub_tasks.description:
Ship feature flag OFF by default → enable in Demo.
 • Monitor OTLP exporter logs and Kusto ingestion errors for 24h.
 • Run the two ticket queries; ensure spans now show both attributes.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Dashboard shows >95% of spans on /clm/Documents/BrowseDocuments.aspx with non-null HTTP_REFERER when header exists.

sub_tasks.name: Gradual rollout to Production
sub_tasks.description: Enable feature flag 25% → 50% → 100% while monitoring ingestion rate and ADX throttling.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: No increase in span drop rate or p95 server latency.

result.explanation:
ADEXS already enriches all server–side spans through `ActivityEnricher.SetTagsWithCommonFields`.  
Adding the two required attributes is therefore only a matter of:

1. Extending the shared OpenTelemetry semantic-convention helper so that the attribute
   names can be referenced from a single place.
2. Reading the headers from the current `HttpContext` (request and response) and
   calling `Activity.SetTag(...)`.

Because `SetTagsWithCommonFields` is invoked **after** the HTTP pipeline has finished
(the method already reads `context.Response.StatusCode`), both the incoming **Referer**
request header and the **Location** response header are available.
